text.section:
The member contributions under subsection (b) of this section:
are designated as employee contributions to be picked up by the employing unit within the meaning of § 414(h)(2) of the Internal Revenue Code and shall be treated as employer contributions in determining tax treatment under that section;
shall reduce the compensation of the member in an amount that equals the member contribution picked up by the employer;
may not be included as gross income of the member until the pickup amounts are distributed or made available to the member;
shall be paid by the State or other approved employer from the same source of funds that is used to pay compensation to the member; and
for purposes of this Division II, shall be treated in the same manner and to the same extent as member contributions made before establishment of the employer pickup program.
